features: 【Large Size for 24 Pairs】The shoe rack for closet measures 43.3"×11.5"×24.5". The height of each layer is close to 6 inches, which allows for at least 6 pairs of shoes to be placed on each layer (including the ground layer).

【Oxford Fabric and Metal Grid Design】 The free-standing shoe rack is designed with 1 layer of metal grid and 2 layers of oxford fabric, which can help store various types of shoes, including high-heeled shoes. This design enriches the storage functions of the shoe rack organizer, creating a clean and orderly space.

【Sturdy & Stable】The shoe rack for closet features rust-proof metal tubes and sturdy metal frame that ensure its stability and prevent deformation. It's sturdy and durable for long-term use. Besides, the Oxford cloth layers can be cleaned easily by wiping with a damp cloth.

【DIY Shoe Rack】 The layers of the metal shoe rack can be disassembled and rearranged to meet your various storage needs like storing boots, bags, suitcases. You can diy this shoe organizer to fit most scenarios, such as garage, entryway, floor, closet, bedroom and so on.

【Easy to Assemble】This shoe rack for closet includes a L-shape wrench, making assembly quick and hassle-free. It is easy to assembly with just 4 steps. Simply follow the instructions and enjoy your new shoe organizer for closet in no time.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars This has cloth shelves. Not what I was expecting or wanting.
reviews.reviewText: I was more than a little disappointed to open this and find that it had nylon cloth shelves. I have had these in the past and found that if sunlight hits the fabric, they fall apart pretty quickly. There is one metal shelf for the bottom, which is weird that they'd mix them together. The shelves are not very tall. So, they're great if you want to get more shoes into a smaller height, but kind of a pain because they are just as tall as shoes, so you have to slide them straight in (squat down). So, these are not going to accommodate bigger shoes. So, those stripper pumps and size 13 trainers gonna have to find a different home.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Simple solution for too many shoes
reviews.reviewText: This shoe rack is simple to assemble using the provided or your own Allen wrench. It's sturdy enough to hold all the shoes you can put on it. But it isn't heavy duty. As long as you don't abuse it this should last many years. At $17 it seems a very good bargain value.
